%% Data Flow Diagram - ODH Notebook Controller (kubeflow)
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (service-ca)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant Webhook as Notebook Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant DSPA as DSPA CR

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 1: Notebook Access (Auth Enabled)
    User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>KRBP: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS (service-ca cert)<br/>Bearer token forwarded
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: TokenReview<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Token valid
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(notebooks.kubeflow.org GET)<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Access granted
    KRBP->>Notebook: Forward to localhost<br/>HTTP/8888, plaintext (loopback)<br/>X-Auth-Request-User header
    Notebook-->>KRBP: Response
    KRBP-->>Gateway: HTTPS Response
    Gateway-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: Notebook Access (Auth Disabled)
    User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>Notebook: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8888, No auth
    Notebook-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over Dashboard,Webhook: Flow 3: Notebook Mutation (Webhook)
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: CREATE/UPDATE Notebook<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutating webhook call<br/>HTTPS/443->8443<br/>TLS (service-ca), API server client cert
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Read ImageStreams, ConfigMaps<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Webhook: Resource data
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Notebook<br/>(sidecar injected, CA certs, image resolved)

    Note over Controller,DSPA: Flow 4: Elyra Pipeline Config Reconciliation
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Read DSPA CR<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: DSPA spec/status
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Read Gateway CR<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Gateway details
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/Update ds-pipeline-config Secret<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
